item.dc:creator: @Nexus1 Nexus_
item.description:
@Nexus1 wrote:

[quote=“Saphire`, post:69, topic:386710”]I can disagree with that, the way it’s written won’t let you add much to the process because it will overflow or allow data to be leaked. Of course you can re write it to perfection, but that would mean a lot of work.

It’s probably best to write your own base, because re writing all of Deltascape would be more work and effort.[/quote]
Well I mean I don’t use DS, but I just don’t like seeing people hate on it. It has capability if you just rewrote a couple classes, and data leaks can be fixed rather quickly.

And when I say DS, I don’t mean the ones with over 500 customs and dclaw 2 hit specials. Im talking about the clean version Delta himself released lastly.

item.title: Summerbright - Korasi, claws, pvp, chaotic, primal - more
item.dc:creator: @Saphire1 Saphire`
item.description:
@Saphire1 wrote:

Nexus_:

No, its not. Just needs more work. I don’t understand why everyone’s fussing about Delta; if you rewrote some login packets and reconfigured their space intake, it would be alright.

I can disagree with that, the way it’s written won’t let you add much to the process because it will overflow or allow data to be leaked. Of course you can re write it to perfection, but that would mean a lot of work.

It’s probably best to write your own base, because re writing all of Deltascape would be more work and effort.
